22/02/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- European Commission Justice Commissioner Franco Frattini arrived in Podgorica on Thursday (February 21st) to officially open talks on alleviating the EU visa regime for Montenegrin citizens. 
Frattini told outgoing Prime Minister Zeljko Sturanovic that it could happen by year's end, adding Montenegro had made commendable progress in meeting necessary criteria.
Separately on Thursday, Frattini opened the National Visa Centre in Skopje, a requirement for starting negotiations to ease Macedonia's visa regime with the EU. 
He also promised the EU would continue to support different programmes to train and reform Macedonian police. 
(Vijesti - 22/02/08; RTCG, Antena M, AP - 21/02/08)
